to|Paulo S\u00e9rgio]] (2011\u20132012)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11095_7077008,00.html | title=Hearts appoint Paulo Sergio | publisher=BSKYB | work=Sky Sports | date=2 August 2011 | accessdate=5 October 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heartsfc.co.uk/articles/20120607/paulo-exits-hearts_2241384_2805297 |title=Paulo exits Hearts |publisher=Heart of Midlothian F.C. |date=7 June 2012 |accessdate=7 June 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120615135442/http://www.heartsfc.co.uk/articles/20120607/paulo-exits-hearts_2241384_2805297 |archivedate=15 June 2012 }}</ref>\n*  [[John McGlynn (Scottish footballer)|John McGlynn]] (2012\u20132013)<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/hearts/9357260/John-McGlynn-named-Hearts-manager.html# | title=John McGlynn named Hearts manager | work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | location=London |date=26 June 2012 | accessdate=26 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/hearts/9900434/Hearts-sack-John-McGlynn.html | title=Hearts sack John McGlynn | work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | location=London | date=28 February 2013 | accessdate=19 March 2013}}</ref>\n*  [[Gary Locke (Scottish footballer)|Gary Locke]] (2013\u20132014)<ref>https://www.scotsman.com/sport/football/hearts/in-full/hearts-gary-locke-not-worried-by-derby-pressure-1-2925473</ref>\n* [[Robbie Neilson]] (2014\u20132016)\n* [[Ian Cathro]] (2016\u20132017)\n* [[Craig Levein]] (2017\u20132019)\n* [[Daniel Stendel]] (2019\u2013)\n{{col-end}}\n\n== Heart of Midlothian Women ==\nIn 2009 Hearts took over Musselburgh Windsor Ladies Football Club and they became [[Hearts Ladies F.C.]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heartsfc.co.uk/articles/20090811/womens-football-club-launched_2241384_1749543 |title=Women's football club launched! |publisher=Heartsfc.co.uk |accessdate=8 November 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120904080211/http://www.heartsfc.co.uk/articles/20090811/womens-football-club-launched_2241384_1749543 |archivedate=4 September 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://scotwomensfootball.com/league-competitions/swpl-2/|title=Scottish Building Society SWPL 2 - Scottish Women's Football|website=Scotwomensfootball.com|accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nThey currently play in the [[Scottish Women's Premier League]] under the name [[Heart of Midlothian W.F.C.|Hearts Women]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.womenspremierleague.co.uk/fixtures-results/|title=Fixtures & Results - Scottish Building Society Scottish Women's Premier League|website=Womenspremierleague/co/uk|accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe team play their home games at Kings Park, [[Dalkeith]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jaxmcmedia.co.uk/swpl-2-2018|title=Jax Mc Media Women's Football Results - Scotland - Jax Mc Media - SWPL 2 - 2018|website=Jax Mc Media Women's Football Results - Scotland - Jax Mc Media|accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n* {{cite book | last = Hoggan | first = Andrew | title = Hearts in Art | type = Hardback | year = 1995 | publisher = Mainstream | isbn = 1-85158-736-5}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Heart of Midlothian F.C.}}\n*[http://www.heartsfc.co.uk/ Official Club website]\n*[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/h/heart_of_midlothian/default.stm BBC My Club Hearts page]\n*[http://soccernet.espn.go.com/team/_/id/262/heart-of-midlothian?cc=5739 Hearts at ESPN]\n*[http://www.londonhearts.com/scores/scores.htm Complete Statistical Record]\n\n{{Heart of Midlothian F.C.}}\n{{Scottish Professional Football League}}\n{{Scottish Premier League}}\n{{Scottish Football League}}\n{{Football in Edinburgh}}\n{{portalbar|Association football|Scotland}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Heart Of Midlothian F.C.}}\n[[Category:Heart of Midlothian F.C.| ]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Edinburgh]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Scotland]]\n[[Category:Associa