ratt (footballer)|David Pratt]] (1935\u20131937)<ref name = \"Introducing the 28 Hearts managers since 1901\"/>\n* [[Frank Moss (goalkeeper)|Frank Moss]] (1937\u20131940)<ref name = \"Introducing the 28 Hearts managers since 1901\"/>\n* [[David McLean (footballer born 1883)|David McLean]] (1941\u20131951)<ref name = \"Introducing the 28 Hearts managers since 1901\"/>\n* [[Tommy Walker (footballer born 1915)|Tommy Walker]] (1951\u20131966)<ref name = \"Introducing the 28 Hearts managers since 1901\"/>\n* John Harvey (1966\u20131970)<ref name = \"Introducing the 28 Hearts managers since 1901\"/>\n* [[Bobby Seith]] (1970\u20131974)<ref name = \"Introducing the 28 Hearts managers since 1901\"/>\n* [[John Hagart]] (1974\u20131977)<ref name = \"Introducing the 28 Hearts managers since 1901\"/>\n* [[Willie Ormond]] (1977\u20131980)<ref name = \"Introducing the 28 Hearts managers since 1901\"/>\n* [[Bobby Moncur]] (1980\u20131981)<ref name = \"Introducing the 28 Hearts managers since 1901\"/>\n* [[Tony Ford (footballer born 1945)|Tony Ford]] (1981)<ref name = \"Introducing the 28 Hearts managers since 1901\"/>\n* [[Alex MacDonald (footballer born 1948)|Alex MacDonald]] (1982\u20131986)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.londonhearts.com/scores/man/alexmacdonald1st.html | title=Alex MacDonald 1st From 10 Dec 1981 | publisher=London Hearts | accessdate=8 October 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Sandy Jardine]] and [[Alex MacDonald (footballer born 1948)|Alex MacDonald]] (1986\u20131988)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.londonhearts.com/scores/man/alexmacdonaldandsandyjardine.html | title=Alex MacDonald and Sandy Jardine From 01 Nov 1986 To 30 Nov 1988 | publisher=London Hearts | accessdate=8 October 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Alex MacDonald (footballer born 1948)|Alex MacDonald]] (1988\u20131990)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.londonhearts.com/scores/man/alexmacdonald2nd.html | title=Alex MacDonald 2nd From 01 Dec 1988 To 09 Sep 1990 | publisher=London Hearts | accessdate=8 October 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Joe Jordan (footballer)|Joe Jordan]] (1990\u20131993)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.londonhearts.com/scores/man/joejordan.html | title=Joe Jordan From 10 Sep 1990 To 03 May 1993 | publisher=London Hearts | accessdate=8 October 2011}}</ref>\n{{col-2}}\n* [[Sandy Clark]] (1993\u20131994)<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/sport/spl/aberdeen/clark-given-the-hearts-hot-seat-on-permanent-basis-1.760255 | title=Clark given the Hearts hot seat on permanent basis | work=Herald Scotland | location=Glasgow | date=11 May 1993 | accessdate=8 October 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football-hearts-dismiss-clark-1424172.html | title=Football: Hearts dismiss Clark |work=The Independent |location=London |date=21 June 1994 | accessdate=8 October 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Tommy McLean]] (1994\u20131995)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.londonhearts.com/scores/man/tommymclean.html | title=Tommy McLean From 01 Jul 1994 To 30 Jun 1995 | publisher=London Hearts | accessdate=8 October 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Jim Jefferies (footballer)|Jim Jefferies]] (1995\u20132000)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.londonhearts.com/scores/man/jimjefferies.html | title=Jim Jefferies From 04 Aug 1995 To 07 Nov 2000 | publisher=London Hearts | accessdate=8 October 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Craig Levein]] (2000\u20132004)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/newsid=251343.html | title=Levein leaves Hearts |publisher=UEFA  | date=29 October 2004 | accessdate=8 October 2011}}</ref>\n* [[John Grant Robertson|John Robertson]] (2004\u20132005)<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/football/2004/nov/03/newsstory.sport3</ref>\n* [[George Burley]] (2005)<ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/h/heart_of_midlothian/4367202.stm | title=Burley in shock exit from Hearts | publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation |work=BBC Sport | date=22 October 2005 | accessdate=5 October 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Graham Rix]] (2005\u20132006)<ref>{{cite news |