{col-end}}\n\n== Heart of Midlothian Women ==\nIn 2009 Hearts took over Musselburgh Windsor Ladies Football Club and they became [[Hearts Ladies F.C.]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heartsfc.co.uk/articles/20090811/womens-football-club-launched_2241384_1749543 |title=Women's football club launched! |publisher=Heartsfc.co.uk |accessdate=8 November 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120904080211/http://www.heartsfc.co.uk/articles/20090811/womens-football-club-launched_2241384_1749543 |archivedate=4 September 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://scotwomensfootball.com/league-competitions/swpl-2/|title=Scottish Building Society SWPL 2 - Scottish Women's Football|website=Scotwomensfootball.com|accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nThey currently play in the [[Scottish Women's Premier League]] under the name [[Heart of Midlothian W.F.C.|Hearts Women]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.womenspremierleague.co.uk/fixtures-results/|title=Fixtures & Results - Scottish Building Society Scottish Women's Premier League|website=Womenspremierleague/co/uk|accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe team play their home games at Kings Park, [[Dalkeith]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jaxmcmedia.co.uk/swpl-2-2018|title=Jax Mc Media Women's Football Results - Scotland - Jax Mc Media - SWPL 2 - 2018|website=Jax Mc Media Women's Football Results - Scotland - Jax Mc Media|accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n* {{cite book | last = Hoggan | first = Andrew | title = Hearts in Art | type = Hardback | year = 1995 | publisher = Mainstream | isbn = 1-85158-736-5}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Heart of Midlothian F.C.}}\n*[http://www.heartsfc.co.uk/ Official Club website]\n*[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/h/heart_of_midlothian/default.stm BBC My Club Hearts page]\n*[http://soccernet.espn.go.com/team/_/id/262/heart-of-midlothian?cc=5739 Hearts at ESPN]\n*[http://www.londonhearts.com/scores/scores.htm C